      <h2>What’s the difference between a résumé and a CV?</h2>
      <h5> April 2, 2018</h5>
      <img src="image/arnel.jpg" alt="My Blog Image" width="600">
          <p>At some point in our job seeking journeys, we’ve all been asked to submit our résumés or CVs. But how many of us assume these documents are essentially the same thing? They are not, and understanding the difference can help you make the case for yourself.<br>

          <P>Over the years, I have reviewed a number of applicants’ résumés and CVs. They have not all been equal. Those of us who have been in the workforce for some time have even noticed changes in what should or should not be included in these documents. If you are newer to the workforce, you may need some pointers on how create your résumé or CV to reflect your awareness of these changes; you want to make the documents represent your best self. But whether you have been doing this for a while or you’re just starting out, this is a great time to take a look at what you have and review it with a critical eye.<br> <br>
