      <h2>For the teens in our lives! Achievement is to Accomplish or Attain by Work or Effort</h2>
      <h5>March 15, 2018</h5>
      <img src="image/teen.jpg" alt="Achievement" width="600">
      <p>What does it mean to achieve? 
You may think that this single question is only asked of you when you are between the ages of 16-18.  It's the notorious question that is echoed from your guidance counselor, parents and that one family member that you were stuck sitting next to at the last family reunion (LOL).  On a serious note, this question may start in high-school, but during the course of your life you will be asked what achievement means to you?  The beauty of achievement is that it is a combination of work and effort.  That's it!!!  There's no financial cost, no special VIP pass or any other secret path to get it.  Through work and effort, you have the ability to attain achievement.

According to Keith D. Harrell, author of "Attitude is Everything for Success" there are three simple exercises that you can do daily to assist in obtaining your goals.  The three basic ideas to manifest what you want to achieve is to Say it, Believe it, and Receive it. <br> <br>
